review_blob: Very good balance between maltiness and hoppiness. Full body, low carbonation, little alcohol but not too much.
Very refeshing! Lots of citrus (mainly grapefruit). Lightly bitter, light sweetness. Medium body, soft carbonation. Excellent IPA!
Very fresh lager! Citrus and grass in the aroma. Lightly bitter, soft carbonation, medium body. One of the best pale lagers Ive ever tasted.
Citrus and grass in the aroma, little caramel, some honey. Medium bitterness. Somewhere between american and english IPA. Soft carbonation, long bitter finish.
Fresh and fruity, lightly bitter, light body, average carbonation. Strong taste of lingonberry, especially after getting a little warmer.
Well balanced sourness and freshness. Lots of taste. Positive surprise, very nice collab.
Compared to its very low alcohol content, it has pretty full body. Citrusy aroma completed with a slight hint of raisin and caramel gives a bit complexity to the beer.

Crazy stuff. Really. First you think this beer has almost gueuze-like smooth sourness, but then hops strikes behind your back and kicks your ass. Its more an IPA than a sour, but apparently a great beer can be a little bit of both. I love complex beers that tells traditions to fuck off, and this motherfucker really does. Love you Stadin Panimo, and always will.
beer_name: Stadin Wild Yeast American Double IPA

review_blob: Very promising beer from this newcomer. Great balance between freshness and bitterness. Strawberry seed, some citrus. Medium bitterness. Rather long finish.
Mild body, littlealcohol, refreshing. Pale. Too pale. Dry, medium sourness. Fizzy. Quite long finish. Saisons are not my favorite kinds of beers usually, but this one kicks ass.

Quite brutal beer. I cant believe that it only has less than 90 IBU. Would have guessed something like 150. Yes, it was very bitter, but also a bit musty. Good debut beer, I am waiting for the next one from Hatebrew guys.
Nice balanced and hoppy IPA from a small brewery. Medium bitterness, lively, semi-long finish,
Little coffee, little chocolate, basement aromas, black,minimal head, medium sourness, light sweetness, full body, soft carbonation. This kind of beer you dont find often.
Some raisin, some alcohol, pale, sparkling, white foam, light sweetness, fizzy. Nice fresh beer for a sunny day.
Caramel, bread, toast, raisin, red, lightly sour, light sweetness, full body, flat, long finish. Something weird that I truly loved in this beer. Just cant describe it.
Citrus, basement aromas, earthy, pale, sparkling, medium sourness, fizzy, medium body. All in all, nice one, but not as good as I hoped itd be.
beer_name: Sierra Nevada / Russian River BRUX Domesticated Wild Ale

review_blob: Roasty, too much coffee, almost black color, medium bitterness, full body, lively, quite long finish. Quite reasoble beer, but not for me.
Some hazelnuts, heavily sour, light sweetness, amazingly tasty long finish.
Hazelnuts in the far end. Medium sweetness, medium sourness, flat, longest finish ever. Great beer from those crazy dutchmen.
Roasty, coffee, black, minimal head, medium bitterness, heavily sour, full body, bitter, long finish. Love this beer I do.
Coffee, little  alcohol, chocolate, raisin. Black, brown foam. Light sweetness, medium bitterness, medium sourness, salty, full body, thick feel, soft carbonation, long finish.
Alcohol, slightly herbs, golden and sparkling, slightly salty, lively carbonation. Strong disappointment.
beer_name: Gouden Carolus Cuvee Van De Keizer Rood/Red

review_blob: Lots of hops. And some more. Very bitter, sour, light sweetness. Fizzy, full body, bitter, long finish. Piece of art.
Very malty, caramel, bread, chocolate, coffee, roasty, some alcohol. Almost black. Medium sweetness, lightly bitter. Full body, average carbonation, long finish.
Bought from nice store in Warsaw. Some grass, slight floral. Lightly bitter, maybe even salty. Little mild taste. Average carbonation,
Bottle no 61812. Caramel, chocolate, little alcohol, raisin, medium sweetness, slightly salty, full body, long finish.
floral, grass, little alcohol, medium sourness, medium bitterness, light sweetness, soft carbonation.
Alcohol, caramel, chocolate, coffee. Black and beautiful. Medium sweetness, medium bitterness. Full body, soft carbonation, long and bitter finish.
One hoppy bastard. Pale, golden, looks just what tastes. Very bitter, salty. Long and bitter finish. Dont have to regret that I carried over the Atlantic. Im in Love.
Chocolate, coffee, bread, alcohol, black, heavy cloying sweetness, soft carbonation, long finish. Very nice and strong christmas beer, makes me happy but doesnt blow my mind.
Feels good in mouth. Some grass, citrus. Light sweetness combined with medium bitterness, maybe slightly salty. Average carbonation. Nice beer for a nice day.
Strong citrus, some grass and herbs. Beautiful browness. Very bitter, medium sourness. Average carbonation. Best IPA you can buy now in Finland in stores.
Herbs and  grass, alcohol, red color, medium bitterness, average carbonation, bitter finish.
Mild banana, almost colorless, light sweetness but tasteless, soft carbonation. Not gonna buy another one.
Fresh citrus, little grass, medium bitterness, average carbonation, long finish. Im lucky I still have three more in my fridge!
Lots of bread, coffee, chocolate, rather roasty. Color is black with white foam. Very sweet, soft carbonation, relatively long finish. Id love to buy another bottle.
Strong grass and some citrus. Looks tempting with its golden color and white foam. Relatively bitter with light sweetness. Feels lively in mouth and has bitter finish. All in all, amazing IPA.
beer_name: Boulevard Smokestack Series - Double Wide I.P.A.

review_blob: Very refeshing IPA, I am sad that I was a car driver and thus able to taste just a little. You want this beer on a sunny summer day. Some grass, more citrus, medium bitterness, lightly bitter, light sweetness.
UPDATED: OCT 5, 2011
Strong coffee, some chocolate, some bread. Not too much of anything. Medium sweetness, lightly sour. Little fizzy and lively, long finish.
Taste like sweet coffee, or maybe rye bread. I really like its heavy cloying sweetness. Minus is that the taste disappears too early, after the super promising start. Still, great beer.

Very easy to drink, and still so tasty. You can never have London Pride too often, and you can drink it anywhere, with anything. You can get drunked with it, you can enjoy it with meal, have one (or two) in a sauna, or just drink it home alone. Im lovin it.
Surprisingly drinkable. Though taste is rather mild, its still more tasty than many of its Finnish competitors. Nothing special, easy to drink. Not good, not bad.
I dont know why, but sometimes I end up drinking this horribly too sweet pear essence liquid when I am getting drunked. However, I NEVER buy this thing myself, so thats a little excuse.
Like mineral water. Very refreshing on a hot day, or in a sauna, but in any other situations I can never recommend this.
Something between chocolate and raisin. Very strong taste, but just a little taste of alcohol though there is over 18% of it. Heavy sweetness. I never could drink whole bottle alone.

In my opinion, this Chang classic is real exception in basic Thai beers. It is rather strong and tasty, and still it is fresh. When I am very thirsty, and water is too expensive, I definitely buy one Chang Classic (if I am in Thailand).
I love this beer. It just feels great in your mouth. The light sweetness takes me to the heaven and thats probably the reason why I buy Franziskaner Hefes all over again.
Im disappointed. Worst Mikkeller Ive ever tasted. Mild and boring. This december I havent tasted any good winter beer, so I really waited for the moment I get to try this one.
